            PreventsFault: FaultCode.TypeMismatch,
            TriggerCondition: "An operation expects elements of a specific type from a collection, but the collection is declared with a different element type.",
            RecoverySteps: ["Change the collection's element type to match what the operation expects", "Or change the operation to use a type-compatible collection"],
            ExampleBefore: "precept Example\nfield Values as set of string\nstate Draft initial\nstate Done terminal\nevent Add(N as number)\nfrom Draft on Add -> add Values Add.N -> no transition",
